The paper discusses tabling, a resolution mechanism for logic programs, which is a topic that falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses techniques for efficient aggregation of answers, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper proposes a formal framework for soundness, which is a topic that is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
